				<position book_orientation="90" place="left_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						Quicquid discitur, docetur, aut exercetur, duo mihi aurea Specula:
						Luminare Minus, et Luminare Maius.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>Whatever is learned, taught, or excercised, I have two golden mirrors: to illuminate less, and to illuminate more. </translation>
