		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position book_orientation="270" place="right_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						Nemo uel sermone promptior; uel ingenio pra[e]gnantior; uel calliditate astutior; uel
						opere agilior; uel omni industria dexterior; uel toto deniq[ue] animi, corporisq[ue]
						habitu viuidior: summa Gallici Pragmatici laus. Nam Galli
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position book_orientation="270" place="intext">
					<marginalia_text>
						omnia amant expedita; et plurimum
						tribuunt dictoru[m], factoru[m]q[ue]
						Celeritati.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>No one is either more prompt in speaking, or more pregnant in intellect, or more astute in shrewdness, or more agile or action, or more skillful in all industry; or
			finally more lively in the whole condition of mind and body: the highest praise for the French pragmatists. For the French love all prompt things; and they bestow
			the greatest number of sayings and deeds with speed.</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
